ostracize /ˈɒstrəˌsaɪz/

BRIT also  ostracise 

1. V-T If someone is ostracized , people deliberately behave in an unfriendly way toward them and do not allow them to take part in any of their social activities. 排斥 [usu passive] 

例： She claims she's being ostracized by some members of her local community. 她声称遭到自己所在社区的一些成员排斥。

